      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Nationalism can be a double-edged sword. On one hand, it fosters a strong sense of identity and unity among citizens, which can lead to social cohesion and national pride. On the other hand, excessive or exclusionary nationalism can lead to xenophobia, conflict, and division between nations. It's important to strike a balance, promoting healthy patriotism while respecting global diversity and cooperation. The perception of nationalism as dangerous largely depends on how it is employed and expressed by policymakers and societies.",
      "source": "target",
